creator: Julius Klausner, jr
description:
LibriVox recording of History of Company B 307th Infantry by Julius Klausner, jr.
Read in English by William A Crenshaw
The history of Company B, 307 Infantry's participation in The First World War. A part of the 77th Division it trained at Camp Upton, New York before leaving for France. - Summary by Bill 2147
For further information, including links to online text, reader information, RSS feeds, CD cover or other formats (if available), please go to the LibriVox catalog page for this recording.

For more free audio books or to become a volunteer reader, visit LibriVox.org.

Download M4B (31MB)
